WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:19.281
The words to which I would like to call your attention this evening are to be found in Paul's epistle to the Romans in chapter 11, reading verses 25, 26 and 27, verses 25, 26 and 27 in the 11th chapter of Paul's epistle to the Romans.

00:20.522 --> 00:28.690
For I would not brethren that ye should be ignorant of this mystery, lest ye should be wise in your own conceits.

00:29.570 --> 00:37.237
the blindness in part is happened to Israel until the fullness of the Gentiles become in.

00:38.098 --> 00:49.770
And so all Israel shall be saved as it is written, there shall come out of Zion the deliverer and shall turn away ungodliness from Jacob.

00:50.470 --> 00:56.336
For this is my covenant unto them when I shall take away their sin."

00:56.917 --> 00:58.418
Now most of you I'm sure will

00:58.562 --> 01:00.805
there in mind the connection of this.

01:01.305 --> 01:06.532
This is one of these great prophetic utterances in the New Testament.

01:07.613 --> 01:12.059
In many ways it is one of the most remarkable prophecies of all.

01:12.900 --> 01:17.405
Certainly one of the great prophecies of the Apostle Paul.

01:18.767 --> 01:23.953
Now let's again remind ourselves of the context and how the Apostle ever came to say this.

01:24.634 --> 01:28.018
He's working out a great argument in this chapter.

01:28.578 --> 01:34.324
It's a part of the great argument that's been going on from the beginning of the ninth chapter.

01:35.666 --> 01:47.058
It's this whole question of the Jews and their relationship to the kingdom of God, especially to the Christian Church, that particular form of the kingdom of God called the Christian Church.

01:48.460 --> 01:57.650
The position he has to deal with is this, that Gentiles were being tempted to say that God had entirely finished with his ancient people.

01:58.274 --> 02:07.108
and that they, the Gentiles, were being called in because there was some inherent superiority in them.

02:07.449 --> 02:10.554
Now, that's the position that the apostle is dealing with.

02:10.574 --> 02:14.700
And in this chapter in particular, he is looking at this whole matter.

02:14.720 --> 02:18.386
And as I reminded you last Friday night, he develops five great arguments.

02:19.027 --> 02:23.094
He says, that must be wrong, where it merely that I myself am a Jew.

02:23.575 --> 02:25.618
And I'm not only a Christian, but an apostle.

02:25.762 --> 02:34.812
Secondly, there is a remnant according to the election of grace of Jews in the Church at the present time, so it's wrong to say that they're all excluded.

02:35.793 --> 02:53.552
The third argument is the argument in verse 16 that it cannot be so as these people attempted to think because the Jews after all have come out of that root and stock of the patriarchs, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, and certain promises made to them.

02:53.853 --> 02:54.994
That makes it impossible.

02:56.066 --> 03:09.483
And then he goes on to say in the fourth place that there is no difficulty about there being brought back into God's favor, and that is because God is the power to do so.

03:09.604 --> 03:11.947
God is able to grasp them in again.

03:12.647 --> 03:23.922
The fifth argument was, which again makes argument number four still more powerful, that God has already done something much more difficult than that, and that is that he's brought in the Gentiles.

03:24.418 --> 03:41.144
if thou were cut out of the olive tree which is wild by nature and were grafted contrary to nature into a good olive tree, how much more shall these which be the natural branches be grafted into their own olive tree?"

03:41.164 --> 03:41.565
Very well.

03:41.605 --> 03:45.250
Now, there are the five arguments.

03:45.310 --> 03:52.882
What he said in the first section of the chapter is that the rejection of Israel is not total.

03:53.026 --> 03:56.890
And in this second section, he's been fighting out that it isn't final.

03:56.950 --> 03:57.831
It's only temporary.

03:58.592 --> 04:02.076
And that's the way in which he's been working out that great argument.

04:02.276 --> 04:09.525
Now then, having done that, he leaves argumentation and moves to the realm of direct assertion.

04:11.066 --> 04:16.092
All he's shown so far is that the restoration of the Jews is possible.

04:16.853 --> 04:18.455
He's even shown that it's probable.

04:19.516 --> 04:21.298
But now he's going on to say,

04:21.378 --> 04:28.846
that it is an absolute certainty and that's what we are dealing with in these verses 25, 26 and 27.

04:29.626 --> 04:44.581
Now it is again most important that we should bear in mind that what the Apostle is dealing with in all these statements is the nation of the Jews considered racially.

04:45.302 --> 04:47.424
He is not dealing with the case of individuals.

04:48.165 --> 04:49.106
He is dealing

04:49.186 --> 04:52.590
with this whole position of this Jewish race.

04:53.671 --> 05:06.124
In other words, as I am trying to show last week and the week before, the apostle is not dealing here with the question of an individual and his salvation.

05:06.144 --> 05:17.397
He is looking at this bulk of the Jew that is outside, and it is about them he is saying that they can be graphed in again.

05:17.797 --> 05:18.578
He is dealing

05:18.658 --> 05:25.626
then with the problem of the Jews, considered in a racial sense, not a matter of individuals very well.

05:27.207 --> 05:32.994
And what he does here, I say, is to give a great prophetic utterance.

05:34.095 --> 05:42.044
What we've got in this 25th verse, and the first part of verse 26, is a great prophecy.

05:43.105 --> 05:44.266
It's no longer argument.

05:44.767 --> 05:47.570
It is a direct prophetic statement.

05:48.354 --> 05:59.489
with respect to these Jews who are now outside and to the effect that they are going to be brought in again, again speaking racially.

05:59.509 --> 06:03.634
Now, someone may put a question at this point and it's a perfectly reasonable question.

06:05.237 --> 06:15.030
If the apostle all along was aware of what he's now going to declare in verse 25, why then did he bother with his five arguments?

06:16.191 --> 06:18.194
Now, I wonder whether that's occurred to any of you.

06:18.850 --> 06:31.466
if the apostle has known all along as he did, that it was in the plan and the purpose of God to bring in the Jews racially considered into the church and back again into his favor.

06:32.747 --> 06:44.982
Well, then why is he bothered to take all this time, the first twenty-four verses of this chapter, in reasoning about it and arguing about it in the way that we've been considering in the five arguments?

06:45.543 --> 06:47.826
Now, I think this is a very important point.

06:49.442 --> 06:52.507
Are we to say that the five arguments are superfluous?

06:53.689 --> 06:55.612
And the answer is of course a decided no.

06:56.895 --> 06:57.315
But why?

06:57.355 --> 07:10.818
Now this again, if I may turn aside for a moment in a digression, this to me is helpful once more in the whole question of our method of biblical study.

07:12.481 --> 07:15.506
The thing to do always with the scripture is to ask it question.

07:17.090 --> 07:21.636
And many people I feel don't profit by their reading of the scriptures because they don't ask questions.

07:22.577 --> 07:24.840
This is the sort of question you ask therefore at this point.

07:25.861 --> 07:40.159
If you, the Apostle Paul, have known this all the time, and it seems to settle everything, that the Jews are going to be brought back, well then why were they in keepers with all those other arguments and decisions?

07:40.799 --> 07:46.066
Now yeah, it seems to me some of the answers, and this is something that we must learn to apply

07:46.146 --> 07:46.947
ourselves.

07:47.949 --> 07:54.399
The first answer is that it is always right to use your reason in these methods.

07:55.280 --> 08:03.713
You see, the apostle is confronted by a criticism, or if you like, by a very dogmatic statement that the Jews are finished with.

08:03.733 --> 08:09.682
They have crucified their Messiah, they are therefore rejected of God, and God has got no further interest in

08:10.114 --> 08:23.126
Now, the apostle's way of dealing with that is not to get up and say, now look here, listen to me, I'm an apostle and I tell you, it's been revealed to me, I make a prophecy, they are going to be brought back and leave it at that.

08:23.346 --> 08:24.047
He doesn't do that.

08:24.688 --> 08:25.068
Why not?

08:25.428 --> 08:32.935
Well, I say because this is a method which is implied everywhere in the Scripture.

08:34.397 --> 08:39.922
You meet a statement like that or an opponent, first of all, on his own ground.

08:41.314 --> 08:42.456
on the grounds of reason.

08:43.437 --> 08:46.321
That's where you start, as the Apostle starts here.

08:47.804 --> 08:52.110
And it's always right to do that, for instance, in the practical application to us.

08:53.092 --> 09:10.738
If a man comes to you who's a critic of Christianity or a critic of a particular doctrine of the Christian faith, and says something which is quite unreasonable, well, point that out to him, you meet him on his own level, if you can show him that what he's saying is patently ridiculous.

09:11.490 --> 09:26.348
Now, for instance, if a man comes to you when you're handling a great chapter such as this and expects you to tell some amusing stories, well, you just point out to him how utterly incongruous it is to do such a thing when you're handling such a high doctrine.

09:26.368 --> 09:29.452
There is no story which can possibly help at this point.

09:29.772 --> 09:33.376
This is something that he men's thought and reason and application.

09:34.157 --> 09:41.266
And a man who finds this kind of thing rather dull, well, he's just betraying that he doesn't know how to think.

09:42.018 --> 09:46.605
You meet him on his own level, and the apostle does that always, and he's done it in this chapter.

09:47.807 --> 09:50.211
He shows them that they're perfectly wrong.

09:50.271 --> 09:52.595
As he says, I am a Christian, myself, they were.

09:53.456 --> 10:00.447
There's one, then he gives them the other four, meeting them on the grounds of sure reason, but not only that secondly.

10:02.230 --> 10:09.842
The apostle is anxious to instruct these Gentiles and to show them that what has happened

10:10.658 --> 10:14.704
is not in any way inconsistent with the Old Testament teaching.

10:16.727 --> 10:19.031
They seem to be dismissing the whole of the Old Testament.

10:20.212 --> 10:21.514
That doesn't matter any longer.

10:21.534 --> 10:25.140
There are still uninstructed Christian people who tend to say that today.

10:25.420 --> 10:26.982
No, the apostle won't have that.

10:27.002 --> 10:28.625
He wants to instruct people.

10:28.645 --> 10:31.048
So he doesn't just leave it at his prophetic utterance.

10:31.489 --> 10:32.190
He says, look here.

10:32.811 --> 10:34.133
Let's work this out together.

10:34.594 --> 10:37.458
And so, as we've seen, he's been able to demonstrate.

10:37.730 --> 10:52.629
that this very thing that has happened has been prophesied by the Old Testament prophets, so that they shouldn't be surprised and indeed they shouldn't misunderstand it because the Old Testament prophets have already dealt with this matter.

10:53.390 --> 11:01.720
Then thirdly, he is most anxious that the Gentiles should be clear in the principles of the teaching.

11:02.781 --> 11:06.546
Now, this is the point that to me is of great importance

11:06.626 --> 11:08.709
and perhaps especially at this present time.

11:11.292 --> 11:16.939
There are people who always want some direct and immediate statement.

11:18.561 --> 11:28.253
There are some people who claim to be unusually spiritual, who are only interested in some direct prophetic utterances as it were, and they tend to exclude everything else.

11:28.893 --> 11:32.197
People who exclude the Bible and say, we're not interested in the Bible.

11:32.478 --> 11:35.922
We get this direct communication, that's the only thing that matters.

11:36.162 --> 11:42.511
Now I feel that that position is refuted completely by the apostle's method in this very chapter.

11:43.192 --> 11:54.529
He not only gives them a prophetic utterance, but he reasons on the basis of the scriptures and with his own understanding almost his own common sense, pointing out facts to them.

11:55.671 --> 12:06.066
And showing how the position they've taken up is quite incongruous with the whole of the teaching of the Old Testament and also with the Christian teaching

12:06.146 --> 12:07.849
at that particular time.

12:07.889 --> 12:11.254
Now then, and we've seen that the apostle doubts that.

12:12.616 --> 12:14.760
He doesn't really make statements to the Gentiles.

12:14.920 --> 12:17.544
He shows them, he gives them his reasons.

12:18.045 --> 12:19.347
He demonstrates it to them.

12:19.687 --> 12:27.279
He works it out with them in detail in the argumentation and always supported by his quotations from the scriptures.

12:27.860 --> 12:34.130
In other words, he really does want these Gentiles to understand this matter,

12:35.138 --> 12:43.429
so that they'll know exactly around they've been in what they've been tending to say and in order that they may be prepared for what he's now going to tell them.

12:45.251 --> 12:50.999
Very well, the final reason, therefore, I would abuse for the apostles method, is this.

12:52.962 --> 12:58.169
That it is never enough for us only to know the truth positively.

12:59.030 --> 13:02.194
We must also have a negative understanding of it.

13:03.074 --> 13:09.221
We must not only be in a position of saying, this is what has been revealed, we must be able to expose error also.

13:10.503 --> 13:14.287
Otherwise, you really won't be able to help people who are in difficulties.

13:15.629 --> 13:24.840
If you have somebody who's in difficulty about a matter and you just make some highly spiritual statement to them, without meeting their position, you're not likely to help them.

13:25.761 --> 13:29.746
But if you can, as it will come down to their level and reasonably throw with them,

13:30.338 --> 13:33.402
and point out the error and where they've gone astray, they'll see it.

13:33.903 --> 13:37.488
And they'll be saved from not only that error, but from similar errors.

13:37.728 --> 13:43.155
You will have introduced them to a method which they can apply in various other cases.

13:43.696 --> 13:47.501
Now, this is to me a very important matter.

13:47.521 --> 13:53.209
That's why it's always vital that we should watch the apostle in his particular method.

13:54.510 --> 14:00.178
Look at the trouble he's taken before he comes to this tremendous statement.

14:00.322 --> 14:05.411
Now, then, having done that, then he comes to the statement.

14:05.431 --> 14:15.187
He puts before them this great prophecy with regard to the future of the Jews considered in a rational sense.

14:15.207 --> 14:17.431
Now, again, let's ask him a question.

14:17.912 --> 14:18.693
Why does he do this?

14:19.695 --> 14:21.197
Why does he tell them this prophecy?

14:21.618 --> 14:26.546
Well, he gives us an explicit answer himself on this occasion, and here it is.

14:27.426 --> 14:32.592
I would not brethren that you should be ignorant of this mystery.

14:32.612 --> 14:38.698
And then he gives the second reason, lest you should be wise in your own conceits.

14:40.100 --> 14:43.704
Now there he gives us, you see, two reasons.

14:43.724 --> 14:46.267
The first is he doesn't want them to be ignorance.

14:47.788 --> 14:50.091
Actually, there is no question about this.

14:51.012 --> 14:56.658
He is implying a figure of speech here which is called

14:57.122 --> 15:02.911
Light at ease means that you make a strong assertion in a negative manner.

15:03.412 --> 15:14.088
We came across our first example of light at ease in the Epistle to the Romans in the first chapter, in verse 16, where the Apostle said, I am not ashamed of the Gospel of Christ.

15:14.528 --> 15:16.692
What he rarely means is that he is very proud of it.

15:17.753 --> 15:21.319
But it's rather a strong and an expressive way of stating a thing.

15:22.000 --> 15:23.602
I think I said on that occasion,

15:23.778 --> 15:33.889
Let me repeat it, as some of you were not present then, I've always regarded this figure of speech called light at ease as the typically English manner of speech.

15:35.451 --> 15:37.313
You put it negatively instead of positively.

15:37.914 --> 15:39.456
I am not ashamed of the gospel.

15:40.657 --> 15:43.120
And you mean, I am tremendously proud of it.

15:43.580 --> 15:45.883
I consider this a very great privilege.

15:47.184 --> 15:52.370
Or if you like a still more humbly example of this very thing, it is like

15:52.514 --> 15:57.380
What I think you would find most doctors will tell you about their patients.

15:58.221 --> 16:03.508
The doctor is treating the patient and he calls one afternoon and he says, how are you feeling?

16:04.870 --> 16:09.115
The patient almost invariably says, I'm no worse thinking.

16:09.135 --> 16:11.979
What the doctor wants them to say, of course, is that they're very much better.

16:12.500 --> 16:17.025
And in the sense that is what they're trying to say, only that they prefer the negative, I'm no worse thinking.

16:17.866 --> 16:20.690
Now, this is an illustration of light at ease.

16:21.698 --> 16:23.661
The apostle says, I don't want you to be ignorant.

16:23.721 --> 16:26.144
What he means is I really want you to know all about this.

16:26.304 --> 16:27.406
I want to instruct him.

16:28.547 --> 16:36.218
I want you to give the – I want you to have the fullest possible information in order that you'll never go wrong in this matter again.

16:36.659 --> 16:40.003
That is undoubtedly what this expression means.

16:40.584 --> 16:43.168
I wouldn't have pretended that he should be ignorant.

16:43.708 --> 16:50.738
We've got other examples of his using the same argument in other epistles as well as in this one.

16:50.914 --> 17:00.046
But then his second reason is, and this is perhaps still more significant, lest you should be wise in your own conceits.

17:01.828 --> 17:08.897
Now, we are clear about this, of course, because this is what Israel has been saying to them from verse 18 to verse 21.

17:09.839 --> 17:15.506
You remember it, first not against the branches, but if thou burst, thou bearest not the root but the root thee.

17:15.714 --> 17:23.423
I will say then the branches were broken off that I might be grafting well because of unbelief they were broken off and their standest by faith.

17:23.623 --> 17:26.006
Here it is, be not high-minded, but fear.

17:27.227 --> 17:33.574
For if God spared not the natural branches, take heed lest he also spare not thee.

17:34.916 --> 17:37.058
You remember the exaltation to humility.

17:38.079 --> 17:43.826
And here he is repeating it, but putting it in rather a blunter and a more direct manner.

17:43.970 --> 17:48.818
I'm telling you this, he says, lest you be wise in your own conceits.

17:50.019 --> 17:52.343
Now these are interesting terms that he uses here.

17:53.665 --> 18:00.195
The word that is used here for wise is the word that is generally used for false wisdom.

18:01.257 --> 18:03.360
Not true wisdom, but false wisdom.

18:04.722 --> 18:07.487
False wisdom accompanied by pride.

18:08.729 --> 18:12.274
That's the thing he tells him that he wants to save them from.

18:12.802 --> 18:23.357
And lest you be wise in your own conceits, really means lest you have this false wisdom in yourselves or before yourselves.

18:23.377 --> 18:39.000
You start picturing them speaking to themselves with this false wisdom, wise in your own conceits, talking to yourself about yourself, with a false wisdom, coughing yourself up in a false manner, misleading yourself.

18:39.020 --> 18:40.722
Now that's what you really mean.

18:41.474 --> 18:44.558
Now, in what respects, well, is he applying this?

18:44.978 --> 18:51.586
In what respects is he trying to save them from being wise in their own conceits?

18:51.606 --> 18:56.252
Well, the first respect is obviously this one.

18:56.272 --> 18:59.035
He wants to disabuse their minds.

19:00.337 --> 19:02.860
They thought that they understood this whole question.

19:03.361 --> 19:11.090
I mean, this question of the position of the Jews and their own position in the Christian Church, they thought they were quite glad about this.

19:11.650 --> 19:12.411
There's no problem.

19:12.611 --> 19:14.213
That's why the apostle takes up the whole thing.

19:15.074 --> 19:17.818
He heard what these kind of people have been saying.

19:18.458 --> 19:19.940
And he says, this is quite wrong.

19:19.980 --> 19:20.861
They think they know.

19:20.881 --> 19:29.592
They think they understand perfectly this whole question of the present position of the Jewish, that God has cast them off and has absolutely finished with them.

19:29.612 --> 19:31.935
And that's their opinion, and they were very confident in it.

19:32.956 --> 19:35.419
They thought they were very wise in their understanding.

19:35.720 --> 19:40.946
He wants to show them that what they thought was the truth was absolutely wrong.

19:41.890 --> 19:44.433
It means that their conceit was wrong.

19:44.834 --> 19:46.857
Their whole understanding of this matter was wrong.

19:47.478 --> 19:49.420
But I think it has a second meaning also.

19:50.962 --> 19:55.288
They thought that they were wise and they were wise in their own conceits in this way.

19:57.271 --> 20:05.422
That they thought that they were in the church and the Jews outside because they'd got a superior understanding.

20:07.044 --> 20:11.410
They'd been able to see the truth of the gospel, whereas the Jews hadn't.

20:12.226 --> 20:23.599
And therefore what accounted for the fact that they were in the Church and the Kingdom of God was their superiority in the matter of understanding and of belief and of faith accompanied by works.

20:25.061 --> 20:29.486
And the Apostle again wants to show them how terribly wrong that is.

20:29.726 --> 20:36.013
He's already done so in detail in verses 16 and onwards, which I've just read to you again.

20:36.033 --> 20:40.018
They were bursting us over against the Jews, and it's all wrong.

20:40.418 --> 20:42.320
They've got nothing to boast about at all.

20:43.381 --> 20:51.849
And any man who thinks that he's a Christian because of any superiority in himself comes under this castigation of the Apostle here.

20:52.770 --> 21:00.258
If you think you're a Christian, because you've got a superior understanding to the other person who's not a Christian, you're quite wrong, altogether wrong.

21:00.618 --> 21:08.466
The Apostle is going to drive that home in a powerful statement in verse 32, for God earth concluded them all in unbelief.

21:08.834 --> 21:10.616
that he might have mercy upon them.

21:11.898 --> 21:15.702
Now then, he says, you've got a quite wrong idea of yourselves.

21:15.722 --> 21:23.751
You've got an inflated notion of yourselves and your understanding, your own inherent ability and your understanding of this position.

21:23.991 --> 21:26.614
It's completely wrong, says the opposite.

21:26.635 --> 21:29.418
And I want to deliver you from that.

21:29.438 --> 21:32.621
This idea of yours, that the Jews have gone out forever.

21:33.202 --> 21:35.104
I want to show you is completely wrong.

21:35.445 --> 21:36.626
And, thirdly, therefore,

21:36.898 --> 21:47.196
He delivers them from this being wise in their own conceits for this reason, that he doesn't want them to be put to shame when the great reality actually takes place.

21:49.099 --> 21:53.166
He knows what's going to happen, so he says, I'm going to tell you now.

21:54.528 --> 21:57.874
Because if I don't tell you, if I don't teach you and instruct you,

21:57.986 --> 22:07.477
And you and your descendants go on saying that you are in the church because you're such wonderful people with such great understanding, with such excellency of morals and so on.

22:08.278 --> 22:16.028
Well then when you see the Jews being brought in as a race, you'll be put ashamed, you'll be made to look ridiculous.

22:16.648 --> 22:21.214
It will be seen and evident to all that you've been run throughout the centuries.

22:21.414 --> 22:23.116
He wants to save them from all that.

22:23.757 --> 22:27.922
So you see, it's not merely a question of delivering them from their ignorance.

22:28.834 --> 22:33.420
He has this great pastoral care for them, and if you like, we can put it like this.

22:33.440 --> 22:42.731
He wants to bring an end to their making fools of themselves by saying something that is completely wrong and prying themselves on their wrongness.

22:43.512 --> 22:47.557
Very well, that is why he's going to give them this information.

22:48.979 --> 22:57.650
The next point, the third point we come to is this, that he tells them that this information that he's going to give them is a mystery.

22:58.658 --> 23:07.049
I would not brethren that he should be ignorant of this mystery, lest you should be wise in your own conceits.

23:07.629 --> 23:17.762
The blindness in part is happened to Israel until the fullness of the Gentiles become in, and so all Israel shall be saved."

23:17.782 --> 23:19.865
Now that's what he calls a mystery.

23:21.267 --> 23:26.834
Here again is a most important term, and it's interesting for many reasons.

23:28.546 --> 23:35.394
You will find in the epistles of this greater puzzle that he uses this word, mystery, fairly frequently.

23:36.435 --> 23:38.057
Why did he do so?

23:38.077 --> 23:50.551
Well, I tend to accept the verdict of the authorities on this matter, that he did so because it was a term that was very much in current use at that time.

23:51.532 --> 23:56.498
It is a well-known fact that in that ancient world, and especially amongst the Gentiles,

23:57.538 --> 24:02.306
There were what were called mystery religions.

24:02.326 --> 24:10.280
In addition to the Jewish religion, there were these other religions called mystery religions.

24:10.300 --> 24:14.007
Now, the epistle to the Colossians deals in particular with them.

